external_knowledge:
- "Population exceeding 100,000" refers to densely populated areas;
- "Recovery rate above 50%" means more than half of the cases have recovered;
- "Hardest hit by the pandemic" refers to provinces with the highest number of cases per 100,000 population.

- "Tide of cases" refers to the average number of cases per 100,000 population;
- "Dawn of 2022" refers to the date January 1, 2022;
- "Risen the highest" indicates the provinces with the highest average case rates.

- "Average number of cases" refers to the mean number of COVID-19 cases per region;
- "Average number of recovered cases" refers to the mean number of recovered cases per region;
- The overall averages are calculated across all regions.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
   FROM cases
   WHERE number_of_cases > (SELECT AVG(number_of_cases) FROM cases);
